[4] Brazil (Ceara)
Date: Sat 18 Oct 2008
Source: Diario do Nordeste [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, summ.
Mod.LJS, edited]
<http://diariodonordeste.globo.com/materia.asp?codigo=581890>


Despite the continuing trend in the drop in the number of cases of
dengue in recent months this year [2008], Ceara recorded 4 new deaths
as a consequence of [dengue] fever with complications. There were 2
deaths in Fortaleza, one in Aracati, and one in Miraima. With this,
the number of deaths from dengue with complications climbs to 12 in 2008.

In the epidemiological week of 12-18 Oct [2008], 24 new cases of the
disease were reported in the state, of which only 3 were confirmed in
the month of September. All occurred in the interior. The month of
October 2008 has just one confirmed case. The data are from the
weekly dengue bulletin released yesterday afternoon [17 Oct 2008] by
the Secretariat of Health of the State.

In total, 6 cases of dengue with complications were confirmed this
week, and 3 cases of suspected DHF were reported, with 2 cases
occurring in the capital and one in the interior. The number of
deaths from DHF remains at 15. In total, there have been 27 deaths
confirmed in the state.

With these cases, Ceara reaches a total of 41 172 laboratory
confirmed cases in 167 municipalities. There remain an additional 18
suspected cases of the disease under investigation, with 16 deaths.

Currently, Fortaleza has the greatest concentration of cases, with
74.36 percent of confirmed dengue cases in the state, with a total of
30 622 occurrences. The neighborhoods with the highest incidences of
dengue are Messejana (1870 cases), Barra do Ceara (1015), Jangurussu
(881), Jardim das Oliveiras (758), and Mondubim (748). The age range
between 10-19 years is the [cohort] most affected by the disease.

[Byline: Karoline Viana]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It appears that the peak of the dengue outbreak in Ceara has passed.

