[5] India (Punjab)
Date: Thu 23 Oct 2008
Source: The Indian Express [edited]
<http://www.indianexpress.com/news/1-dead--138-confirmed-cases-in-Mohali--dengue-on-the-rise/376944>


The dreaded dengue fever has taken its toll in Mohali. A resident of
Phase I, a woman in her early 30s, died on late Tuesday night [21 Oct
2008] after a drastic fall in her platelet count at the Fortis
Hospital. The woman was suffering from acute fever since 14 Oct
[2008] and had initially taken medication from a private practitioner
in Phase VI, who then referred her to the PGI, Chandigarh, or Fortis
Hospital on 16 Oct [2008], said area municipal councilor Rajinder
Prasad Sharma while speaking to Newsline.

In a contrasting statement, Fortis Hospital medical director Dr Ashok
V Chordiya claimed the patient was brought to the hospital only on
Tuesday [21 Oct 2008] and had died within 8 hours of hospitalization.
"She came with acute fever, and her platelet count was very low,
which is believed to be cause of death," revealed Dr Chordiya.

The DHO [district health officer] revealed that on coming to know
about the dengue death from civil surgeon Dr Avtar Singh, he sent a
team of officials, led by epidemiologist Dr Sunita Paul, to visit the
area. "Our team was stunned to find the larvae of the dengue [virus
transmitting mosquito _Aedes_] in stagnant water at the victim's
house," said Dr Surila. "We also carried out fogging in the house
besides undertaking fever survey in the area," said the DHO. He added
that no other member of the victim's family was found suffering from fever.

Though officially it was the 1st dengue death in Mohali, a young
woman had also died due to suspected dengue nearly a fortnight ago at
the PGI. No confirmation was received from the PGI on a query posed
by the Mohali district health department, said District Health
Officer (DHO) Dr S P Surila.

The official count of confirmed dengue patients reported from Mohali
has touched 138, confirmed the DHO. A number of suspected dengue
patients, however, continue to pour into private and Government hospitals.

--
