[6] Pakistan (Karachi)
Date: Tue 21 Oct 2008
Source: The News [edited]
<http://www.thenews.com.pk/daily_detail.asp?id=142250>


Around 17 new suspected dengue fever cases were reported from
different parts of the city [Karachi] on Monday [20 Oct 2008],
according to the health department spokesman. About 11 patients were
shifted to Abbasi Shaheed Hospital, 2 each at Ziauddin Hospital and
Jinnah Post-Graduate Medical Centre, respectively, and one each at
Civil Hospital, Karachi and Sindh Government Qatar Hospital. The
spokesman said that, so far, around 953 suspected dengue fever cases
have been reported this year [2008], out of which 324 were positive
dengue fever cases.

--
